{"word":"εἰλύω","slug":"εἰλύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εἰλύω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εἴλω'><el>εἴλω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to enfold, enwrap</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be wrapt</i> or <i>covered</i>, <el>νεφέληι εἰλυμένος ὤμους</el>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, also, = <el>ἰλυσπάομαι</el>, <i>to crawl</i> or <i>wriggle along</i>, of a lame man, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b> <el>εἰλυσθείς</el> means <i>rolled up, crouching</i>.<p/></div>"}]}